  "prompt": "Which is the best laptop under 40000 INR?",
  "response": "When looking for the best laptop under 40000 INR, you should consider factors such as performance, battery life, build quality, and display. Here are a few top recommendations that fit within your budget:\n\n1. **Acer Aspire 5**:\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 3250U or Intel Core i3\n   - **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 256GB SSD\n   - **Display**: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - **Pros**: Good build quality, decent performance for everyday tasks, and a reliable battery life.\n\n2. **Lenovo Ideapad S145**:\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 or Intel Core i3\n   - **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 1TB HDD or 256GB SSD\n   - **Display**: 15.6-inch HD or Full HD\n   - **Pros**: Affordable, good battery life, and suitable for students and basic office work.\n\n3. **HP 15s**:\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 or Intel Core i3\n   - **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 256GB SSD\n   - **Display**: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - **Pros**: Sleek design, lightweight, and good performance for the price.\n\n4. **Dell Vostro 3405**:\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 3 or Intel Core i3\n   - **RAM**: 4GB or 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 256GB SSD\n   - **Display**: 14-inch Full HD\n   - **Pros**: Compact and portable, suitable for business use, and reliable performance.\n\nAmong these options, the **Acer Aspire 5** often stands out due to its balance of performance and price. If you can find a model with an AMD Ryzen processor and 8GB of RAM, it will offer better multitasking capabilities and smoother performance for everyday tasks.\n\nAlways check the latest reviews and prices, as they can fluctuate, and make sure to buy from reputable sellers to ensure you get a good warranty and after-sales service.",
